<Base title="About">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>Systems engineer working across security, AI inference, and RF. This site documents the projects, hardware, and logs.</p>

  <h2>Technical Background</h2>

  <h3>Areas of Focus</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Security:</strong> GPU-accelerated IDS, red-team simulations, adversarial networks</li>
    <li><strong>ML/AI:</strong> Local LLM inference, jailbreak eval, spiking neural networks</li>
    <li><strong>Hardware:</strong> PCIe passthrough, InfiniBand/RDMA, thermal management</li>
    <li><strong>RF:</strong> LEO satellite comms, SDR, antenna systems</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Tools & Stack</h3>
  <p class="tech-line"><em>Languages:</em> Python, C/CUDA, Bash, Verilog</p>
  <p class="tech-line"><em>Platforms:</em> Proxmox VE, CUDA, InfiniBand, llama.cpp, Linux KVM</p>
  <p class="tech-line"><em>Hardware:</em> Xeon E5-v3, Tesla P40, ConnectX-3, RTL-SDR</p>

  <h2>Current Work</h2>

  <p>Private AI inference lab on local hardware, LEO satellite ground station, and GPU-accelerated network defense — all built on the Hephaestus platform.</p>

